div.p:
But bee warned and armed against his tentations;


for bee assured if thou once yeeld to neglect praying to God, but one halfe houre, when that time comes thou shalt finde thy selfe farre more vnapt, and thy heart more dull to pray than before: whereas if thou disposest thy selfe to pray, though thou beest heauy and vncheerefull in it, yet God, who searches the heart, and sees thy desire to pray, though thou canst not, will enlighten thee and prepare thy heart against the next time, that thou shalt finde comfort. Therefore, take heed the Deuill


deceiue you not, for you see his malice is not small that seekes to cousen you of all happinesse present and to come: For bee assured you can take no true ioy in earthly pleasures, no longer than you seeke after heauenly.
